longBusinessSummary: Bangkok Dusit Medical Services Public Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates hospitals in Thailand and internationally. The company owns and manages 6 hospital groups, including Bangkok Hospital Group, Samitivej Hospital Group, BNH Hospital, Phyathai Hospital Group, Paolo Hospital Group, and Royal Hospital Group. It operates holistic clinical wellness. In addition, the company operates hotels and restaurant; sells health and cosmetic products; provides accounting, health insurance, laboratory services, investment, information technology, training, skin and aesthetics telemedicine, genome sequencing, insurance brokerage, air transportation, facility management, and property management services, as well as asset management services; and manufactures and distributes medicine and pharmaceutical products and medical equipment. Further, it is involved in the e-commerce and real estate business. Bangkok Dusit Medical Services Public Company Limited was incorporated in 1969 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.
